spec: agent-core.ai-docs/v1
namespace: "Application\\Handler"
fqcn: "Ineersa\\AgentCore\\Application\\Handler"
updatedAt: 2026-04-20
description: "Handler infrastructure — command routing, extension registries, LLM/tool execution workers, outbox projectors, event dispatching, step dispatch, locking, idempotency, replay, tool batch collection, bounded parallel dispatch, and idempotency result store."
files[25]{file,type,summary}:
  CommandHandlerRegistry.php,final class,The CommandHandlerRegistry acts as a central lookup mechanism for resolving command handlers by their specific kind. It maintains a registry of handler instances to facilitate efficient dispatching within the application's command handling pipeline.
  CommandRouter.php,final class,"The CommandRouter class acts as a central dispatcher for ApplyCommand instances, routing them to appropriate handlers based on command kind. It leverages a CommandHandlerRegistry to resolve specific handler implementations and validates command options before routing."
  EventSubscriberRegistry.php,final class,The EventSubscriberRegistry acts as a centralized registry for managing event subscribers within the application's handler layer. It stores a collection of subscribers and provides a mechanism to retrieve them based on specific event types. This design facilitates decoupled event handling by allowing components to query for relevant subscribers dynamically.
  ExecuteLlmStepWorker.php,readonly final class,This class serves as a message handler for executing LLM steps within the agent execution domain. It coordinates with the platform to perform the step logic and dispatches the resulting state updates via a dedicated command bus.
  ExecuteToolCallWorker.php,readonly final class,"This class acts as a message handler for the agent execution bus, processing tool call commands by delegating execution to a dedicated tool executor. It coordinates the invocation of external tools and manages the resulting state updates within the agent's runtime context."
  HookDispatcher.php,readonly final class,The HookDispatcher class orchestrates the execution of registered hook subscribers by mapping hook names to their corresponding handlers. It leverages a subscriber registry to identify relevant hooks and an event dispatcher to trigger the associated logic with provided context data.
  HookSubscriberRegistry.php,final class,The HookSubscriberRegistry maintains a registry of hook subscribers to facilitate event-driven dispatching within the application. It provides a lookup mechanism to retrieve specific subscribers associated with a given hook name.
  JsonlOutboxProjectorWorker.php,readonly final class,The JsonlOutboxProjectorWorker consumes ProjectJsonlOutbox messages to persist event data into a JSONL outbox store. It coordinates the projection of domain events by writing to the outbox and logging execution details via a run log writer.
  LatencyHistogram.php,final class,This class records latency observations and exposes histogram-style snapshots.
  MercureOutboxProjectorWorker.php,readonly final class,This class acts as a worker that processes Mercure outbox projection messages by retrieving pending events from the outbox store. It publishes these events via the run event publisher to ensure consistent delivery to Mercure subscribers.
  MessageIdempotencyService.php,final class,Ensures message idempotency by tracking processed execution keys within specific scopes and run contexts. It prevents duplicate processing of identical idempotency keys for the same logical operation.
  OutboxProjector.php,readonly final class,The OutboxProjector class processes a batch of domain events by persisting execution logs and publishing corresponding runtime events. It acts as a bridge between the outbox storage mechanism and external consumers via the event publisher.
  ReplayService.php,readonly final class,ReplayService reconstructs agent run state by replaying historical events from the event store and run logs. It verifies data integrity and rebuilds prompt state to ensure consistency across sequences.
  RunDebugService.php,readonly final class,"This service provides read-only debugging views for run state, replay streams, and hot prompt snapshots."
  RunEventDispatcher.php,readonly final class,The RunEventDispatcher class acts as an application-level facade for routing RunEvent instances to registered subscribers. It leverages an EventSubscriberRegistry to identify relevant handlers and delegates execution to a standard EventDispatcherInterface. This design decouples the specific event type from the underlying dispatching mechanism.
  RunLockManager.php,readonly final class,"The RunLockManager provides a mechanism to execute critical sections of code exclusively for a specific run ID using distributed locking. It leverages a LockFactory to acquire locks with a configurable time-to-live, ensuring thread-safe or process-safe execution of run-specific logic."
  RunMetrics.php,final class,This class collects in-process runtime metrics for run orchestration and workers.
  RunTracer.php,final class,This class emits lightweight structured tracing spans for run processing paths.
  StepDispatcher.php,readonly final class,The StepDispatcher class orchestrates the execution of agent steps by routing effects and messages to distinct message buses. It decouples side-effect processing from publishing logic by delegating to separate MessageBusInterface instances.
  ToolBatchCollectOutcome.php,readonly final class,"A readonly value object representing the outcome of a tool batch execution within the agent core application. It encapsulates execution status flags, ordered results, and side-effect payloads for downstream processing. Designed to provide a structured, immutable contract for communicating batch processing states."
  ToolBatchCollector.php,final class,"The ToolBatchCollector aggregates individual tool calls into batches based on run, turn, and step identifiers, enforcing a configurable maximum parallelism limit. It tracks expected batches and collects results to determine when a batch is complete and ready for dispatch."
  ToolCatalogResolver.php,final class,Resolves tool catalog definitions by iterating over registered providers and aggregating their payloads. Ensures schema stability for each tool definition by computing and verifying a deterministic fingerprint.
  ToolExecutionPolicyResolver.php,readonly final class,"Resolves execution policies for tools by combining a default configuration with specific overrides. It determines the operational mode, timeout, and parallelism constraints for a given tool name."
  ToolExecutionResultStore.php,final class,"This class provides a caching layer for tool execution results, enabling efficient retrieval of previously computed outputs. It supports lookup by run and tool call identifiers, as well as by tool name and idempotency keys to prevent redundant execution."
  ToolExecutor.php,final class,"The ToolExecutor class orchestrates the execution of tool calls within an agent core, handling policy resolution, argument validation, and result caching. It integrates with the Symfony Toolbox for tool invocation and manages execution metadata, including timeouts, parallelism, and cancellation. The class ensures consistent tool result formatting and applies post-execution hooks to the assistant message context."